reviews.review_text: Best Wharf Rat Ever If you don't know this show intimately as I do, you need to spend some time with it.  The energy is off the charts.  The final 30 minutes (Other One, Wharf Rat, Sugar Mag) are maybe the hottest post drums in the history of the GD.  Listen to the first jam in Wharf Rat, completely sublime.  The Sugar Mag rocks the rafters.  In the first set, you will hear quite possibly the hottest Let it Grow and the most wailing Deal ever.  Sure, it's a little sloppy here and there (see:Bertha).  But this is high octane, full on balls to the wall Vista Cruiser Grateful Dead.  Turn it to Eleven and enjoy

Highly Collectible Slow start with an uneven Jack Straw.  I had to snicker at the not-in-sink vocals at the end. Quite funny. But the show quickly gets better with a blistering Big River and rousing Let It Grow > Deal to close the set.  Luv the transition to Deal.

Very good second set and encore.  Overall, I’m willing to sneak in five stars with the quality of the show and matrixed sound, mindful that the opener was a little off.
